com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class StandardFixSerializationTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.StandardFixSerializationTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFromMessageTransformer

    public class StandardFixSerializationTransformer
extends Object
implements IFromMessageTransformer
    Transforms message into standard FIX bytes - ie tag=value separated by SOH characters.

    By default all fields in the message are serialized. Extra fields commonly used in FIX communication, such as body length, checksum etc, can be configured to be ignored.

    Instances of this class are thread-safe.

      • StandardFixSerializationTransformer

        public StandardFixSerializationTransformer(Set<Integer> tagsToIgnore,
                                           boolean reorderTags,
                                           boolean reuseBytes)
        AbstractConfigurable serialization.
        Parameters:
        tagsToIgnore - these tags won't be serialized
        reorderTags - If true the message tags will be grouped into header/body/footer sections according to the FIX spec before serializing the message.
        reuseBytes - If true and message rawOutBytes are set, reuse raw out bytes instead of serializing the message.
        See Also:
        IFIXMessageSpecifics.getRawOutBytesNotIncludingBodyLengthBeginStringCheckSum()

      • toObject

        public Object toObject(IFIXMessage source,
                       Object target,
                       Set<Integer> effectiveSecureTags)
                throws IllegalArgumentException,
                       UnsupportedOperationException,
                       CryptoException
        Returns a BytesSegment containing the serialized message as FIX bytes.

        If target is null, an internal BytesSegment is created to store the result.

        If the supplied BytesSegment in target is not large enough to hold the serialized bytes, it will automatically be grown by calling the BytesSegment.grow(int, boolean) method on the supplied BytesSegment.

        Parameters:
        source - FIX message to be serialized.
        target - BytesSegment to use to store serialized bytes, or null.
        effectiveSecureTags - the transformer will ignore any tag in this set
        Returns:
        BytesSegment containing the serialized bytes (will be 'target' if not null).
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If target is not a BytesSegment, or if it was not possible to convert the message.
        UnsupportedOperationException - Never.
        CryptoException - Never
